reviews.review_text:
3-27-87 Nice hot show. Bad recording. I'd hate to hear what this sounded like before wizard C Miller got his hands on it. Definitely go for
the aud on this one friends.

Whistle through your teeth & spit! Damnit!  Listen to the man.  This is a great version of Touch of Grey.  Just listen to the crowd going crazy.  I'd give anything to have been there.  And come on, Morning Dew, wowsa.  What a ripped away version, minus the small misstep at the peak which is fine.  It was a nice recovery and I hung on every note until they got back on track.

So Glad this is good, 86 seemed way off and tragic seemed to us something was very wrong on the 86 spring tour? or was it me and my adolescent mood? Or both? That was a while after "Suppos Playin" became a song/thing.... Glad to see when they got back a year later after the Trouble that they recalled who they were and all that, so they could do what they do, as can be seen here in high def as my cat says.  its useful when u try to get through the day. U can make fun of Hartford all day, but you'd miss this, and possibly a latter day jerry led St. Stephen....like I did.
